description: Lexicographically earliest infinite sequence such that for all i, j >= 1, a(i) = a(j) => f(i) = f(j), with f(1) = 1, and for n > 1, f(n) = [A278226(A328768(n)), A374212(n), A374213(n)], where A328768 is the first primorial based variant of the arithmetic derivative, and A374212 and A374213 are its 2- and 3-adic valuations.
